Package ptdb.common.exception

The common/exception package.

See: Description

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    CircularDependencyException
    Exception thrown when an attempt to save a model with references or import a model by reference would result in a circular dependency.
    DBConnectionException
    Exception for all the exceptions raised during XML database connection related operations.
    DBExecutionException
    Exception class for all the exceptions raised during XML database connection related operations.
    DBModelNotFoundException
    Exception class that is thrown if the model is not found in the database.
    IllegalNameException
    Exception for illegal names for attributes, model or other values.
    ModelAlreadyExistException
    Exception class for thrown when creating a model that already exist in the database.
    SearchCriteriaParseException
    The exception for any parsing error happens during the parsing of the stored search criteria.
    UnSavedParentModelsException
    Exception when there is parent model opening and unsaved, while the user wants to save the sub model.
    XMLDBModelParsingException
    Exception for document or MOML parsing errors.
